The paper discusses a dependent random sampling technique called pipage rounding and its applications in various areas such as submodular functions, matrix analysis, and geometric questions. These topics are closely related to data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), computational complexity (cs.CC), and computational geometry (cs.CG). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
